hopobject.body: Have you seen any good films recently? formula r3 Both indices opened sharply up on Thursday after remarks Bernanke made Wednesday evening about the potential for the Fed to taper its $85 billion monthly purchases of bonds and other securities, popularly known as quantitative easing. The Fed's purchases have have greatly boosted stock markets by lowering interest rates and making equities more appealing to investors than fixed-income investments. Speaking at a National Bureau of Economic Research conference on Wednesday, Bernanke said he thinks the unemployment rate of 7.6 percent "overstates" the health of the job market, and that "a highly accommodative policy is needed for the foreseeable future."
